00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:40,665 --> 00:01:42,065
YUNSHAN ZIZHU RESTAURANT

2
00:01:42,145 --> 00:01:43,425
It's cold outside.

3
00:01:43,505 --> 00:01:44,625
How about I drive you?

4
00:01:45,265 --> 00:01:48,025
No need. My company is close by.
It's just a short walk.

5
00:01:48,545 --> 00:01:49,825
Go on. Get back to work.

6
00:01:53,065 --> 00:01:53,905
You…

7
00:02:05,905 --> 00:02:07,625
So, since that time,

8
00:02:08,744 --> 00:02:10,385
you had been planning to kill Captain Ran?

9
00:02:15,825 --> 00:02:17,465
Quite the opposite.

10
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:20,745
When I discovered that he was a cop,

11
00:02:21,625 --> 00:02:23,145
I actually stopped worrying.

12
00:02:24,145 --> 00:02:25,305
At the time, I thought

13
00:02:25,385 --> 00:02:28,065
Qiao Suqing must have been acting.

14
00:02:29,225 --> 00:02:32,425
She wanted to use the cop
as a cover for herself.

15
00:02:33,105 --> 00:02:35,465
She was carrying too many secrets.

16
00:02:36,385 --> 00:02:39,385
How could she possibly be with a cop?

17
00:02:40,225 --> 00:02:42,825
But over the following months,

18
00:02:42,905 --> 00:02:45,625
Qiao Suqing clearly became cold toward me.

19
00:02:46,305 --> 00:02:49,385
I'd send her messages,
but she rarely replied.

20
00:02:49,985 --> 00:02:51,905
When she answered the phone,
she'd say she was working.

21
00:02:53,345 --> 00:02:55,145
She always said she was busy.

22
00:02:57,345 --> 00:02:58,185
She changed.

23
00:02:58,785 --> 00:03:01,985
<i>I couldn't help myself,</i>
<i>so I went back to Weiyang.</i>

24
00:03:02,505 --> 00:03:04,545
<i>I wanted to give her a surprise.</i>

25
00:03:05,585 --> 00:03:07,385
<i>I wanted to spend</i>
<i>the Chinese New Year with her.</i>

26
00:03:07,465 --> 00:03:09,865
Hello. Please wrap these two up for me.

27
00:03:11,185 --> 00:03:13,105
Do you want to wear it now?
I can take the tags off for you.

28
00:03:13,785 --> 00:03:15,545
Sure. Thanks.

29
00:03:26,225 --> 00:03:27,305
Welcome.

30
00:03:49,385 --> 00:03:51,425
<i>I can never forget</i>

31
00:03:51,945 --> 00:03:54,305
<i>the look in her eyes back then.</i>

32
00:03:56,025 --> 00:03:58,385
<i>I had never seen her smile so happily.</i>

33
00:04:01,665 --> 00:04:03,985
I thought about it for two whole days.

34
00:04:06,305 --> 00:04:08,705
In the end, I decided
I had to go talk to her.

35
00:04:09,945 --> 00:04:11,665
She's in great danger now.

36
00:04:11,745 --> 00:04:13,905
I must protect her.

37
00:04:16,465 --> 00:04:18,465
But then, right at that moment,

38
00:04:20,985 --> 00:04:23,265
I received a call from her.

39
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:27,945
You're going to turn yourself in?

40
00:04:29,785 --> 00:04:31,785
I've confessed everything to the police.

41
00:04:33,465 --> 00:04:35,265
I'm the one who killed everyone.

42
00:04:36,465 --> 00:04:37,465
Including you.

43
00:04:39,705 --> 00:04:41,665
When do you plan to turn yourself in?

44
00:04:43,225 --> 00:04:44,305
Tomorrow morning.

45
00:04:49,105 --> 00:04:52,665
Why didn't the cop just arrest you?

46
00:04:53,265 --> 00:04:54,825
He promised me

47
00:04:57,825 --> 00:05:00,025
that I could finish
this Chinese New Year's Eve.

48
00:05:04,265 --> 00:05:06,225
I'll come find you right now.

49
00:05:06,305 --> 00:05:07,145
I'll stay with you.

50
00:05:08,305 --> 00:05:11,105
Meng, don't come.

51
00:05:12,945 --> 00:05:16,345
<i>I already promised that cop</i>
<i>that I wouldn't run.</i>

52
00:05:17,345 --> 00:05:18,545
He also promised me

53
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,305
that tonight,

54
00:05:23,065 --> 00:05:24,465
he would spend
the Chinese New Year with me.

55
00:05:26,345 --> 00:05:27,705
<i>I had made an appointment with him.</i>

56
00:05:28,625 --> 00:05:30,665
<i>When I finish my part-time job tonight,</i>

57
00:05:32,065 --> 00:05:33,185
<i>he'll come to pick me up.</i>

58
00:05:33,825 --> 00:05:35,065
Tomorrow morning,

59
00:05:36,785 --> 00:05:38,705
he'll go with me to turn myself in.

60
00:05:41,185 --> 00:05:42,225
<i>Meng,</i>

61
00:05:43,585 --> 00:05:46,225
<i>you must live a good life.</i>

62
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:50,185
Sister, wait for me.

63
00:05:50,705 --> 00:05:52,985
I'm taking the train tomorrow morning
back to Weiyang.

64
00:05:53,665 --> 00:05:56,345
-<i>I'll go with you to turn yourself in.</i>
-No.

65
00:05:57,105 --> 00:05:58,065
Absolutely not.

66
00:05:58,145 --> 00:06:00,585
<i>You finally have a home of your own.</i>

67
00:06:00,665 --> 00:06:03,625
<i>Just stay there and live well.</i>

68
00:06:04,465 --> 00:06:06,225
Live the life you want.

69
00:07:01,945 --> 00:07:04,625
Previously,
when I was tailing Qiao Suqing,

70
00:07:05,905 --> 00:07:07,865
I visited the place
where she worked part-time.

71
00:07:10,145 --> 00:07:12,505
I noticed a section of the road
with a construction site in the middle.

72
00:07:14,825 --> 00:07:16,905
So I thought of using my old method,

73
00:07:18,465 --> 00:07:20,145
which was staging an accident.

74
00:07:21,505 --> 00:07:23,185
To ensure success,

75
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,865
I went back to the mall.

76
00:07:27,465 --> 00:07:28,825
I bought a wig,

77
00:07:29,865 --> 00:07:34,025
and I even bought the same Bowls coat
and red scarf as Qiao Suqing.

78
00:07:34,825 --> 00:07:36,385
I dressed up just like her.

79
00:07:37,545 --> 00:07:38,425
First,

80
00:07:38,505 --> 00:07:41,785
it helped me better attract
the attention of that cop.

81
00:07:42,305 --> 00:07:43,345
Second,

82
00:07:44,545 --> 00:07:46,025
if the plan failed,

83
00:07:47,545 --> 00:07:49,545
I could still pin the blame on her.

84
00:07:50,425 --> 00:07:52,705
You kept insisting
that you wanted to protect Qiao Suqing.

85
00:07:52,785 --> 00:07:54,105
Why would you try to frame her?

86
00:07:54,185 --> 00:07:55,345
Why do you think!

87
00:07:56,705 --> 00:07:58,065
It was for our safety.

88
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:01,665
I killed Yao,

89
00:08:02,425 --> 00:08:05,145
I killed Xu Zhihong,
and I killed Wu Shanlong.

90
00:08:07,985 --> 00:08:08,985
But what about her?

91
00:08:11,145 --> 00:08:14,225
She knew clearly that the cop
was investigating us,

92
00:08:15,345 --> 00:08:16,825
yet she still stayed with him.

93
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:19,665
She lied to me.

94
00:08:19,745 --> 00:08:21,225
She betrayed me.

95
00:08:21,305 --> 00:08:22,625
She deserves it.

96
00:08:22,705 --> 00:08:24,105
She deserves it!

97
00:08:51,505 --> 00:08:52,785
SIR

98
00:09:02,745 --> 00:09:03,985
Qiao.

99
00:09:05,585 --> 00:09:06,745
Qiao, no!

100
00:10:01,025 --> 00:10:03,625
SIR

101
00:10:54,505 --> 00:10:55,385
Xu…

102
00:11:21,185 --> 00:11:24,025
I should have killed Ran long ago.

103
00:11:26,025 --> 00:11:30,065
If not for him,
Qiao Suqing would never have betrayed me.

104
00:11:30,585 --> 00:11:32,905
She would still be my elder sister,

105
00:11:32,985 --> 00:11:34,905
and I would still be her younger sister.

106
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:37,945
We could have lived happily

107
00:11:39,545 --> 00:11:41,625
at home together.

108
00:11:41,705 --> 00:11:43,465
Xu Meng, you're not human!

109
00:11:43,545 --> 00:11:45,465
-Calm down.
-Do you have any humanity at all?

110
00:11:45,545 --> 00:11:47,425
-Xiaohe.
-You're the one who killed Uncle Ran!

111
00:11:47,505 --> 00:11:50,305
You're a monster. A monster!

112
00:11:51,305 --> 00:11:54,065
Xu Meng, you have lost your mind
and all humanity.

113
00:11:54,145 --> 00:11:55,145
For your own selfish desires,

114
00:11:55,225 --> 00:11:56,945
you've openly committed
numerous atrocities.

115
00:11:57,025 --> 00:11:58,985
Your methods were cruel,
and your crimes heinous.

116
00:11:59,065 --> 00:12:01,785
You've harmed so many people
and so many families.

117
00:12:01,865 --> 00:12:04,345
You didn't even spare
the innocent Captain Ran or the child.

118
00:12:04,425 --> 00:12:07,185
This is unconscionable. You are pure evil!

119
00:12:33,385 --> 00:12:34,305
Where is it?

120
00:12:54,745 --> 00:12:57,665
<i>No reason is an excuse to break the law.</i>

121
00:12:58,185 --> 00:13:00,985
<i>No crime is ever truly foolproof.</i>

122
00:13:01,065 --> 00:13:02,545
<i>Crime always leaves a trace.</i>

123
00:13:03,545 --> 00:13:06,705
<i>No one escapes the long arm of the law.</i>

124
00:13:07,225 --> 00:13:11,265
<i>Anyone who commits a crime</i>
<i>will be exposed to the law,</i>

125
00:13:11,345 --> 00:13:15,945
<i>exposed to justice,</i>
<i>and exposed to the light of day.</i>

126
00:13:23,465 --> 00:13:26,345
NEW YORK BLOCK

127
00:13:45,705 --> 00:13:46,745
Xiaohe.

128
00:13:48,585 --> 00:13:49,545
I'm sorry.

129
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:53,825
Please also tell Uncle He that I'm sorry.

130
00:13:55,785 --> 00:13:57,545
Everything was my fault.

131
00:13:58,305 --> 00:13:59,905
I brought this on myself.

132
00:14:00,825 --> 00:14:02,305
It's only natural

133
00:14:03,225 --> 00:14:04,665
that you hate me.

134
00:14:05,665 --> 00:14:06,665
Qiao Suqing,

135
00:14:07,905 --> 00:14:08,865
I won't hate you.

136
00:14:09,945 --> 00:14:12,785
The law will judge everything you've done.

137
00:14:13,465 --> 00:14:17,105
I will completely forget
the Qiao Suqing standing before me.

138
00:14:20,025 --> 00:14:22,985
I will only remember that summer of 1997

139
00:14:24,465 --> 00:14:26,985
and the Ms. Qiao who took care of me
all day and all night.

140
00:14:50,505 --> 00:14:51,345
Thank you.

141
00:15:07,705 --> 00:15:10,425
<i>When their legal rights are violated,</i>

142
00:15:10,505 --> 00:15:12,785
<i>the law is the only weapon</i>
<i>to protect oneself.</i>

143
00:15:13,865 --> 00:15:15,785
<i>But in the June 30th case,</i>

144
00:15:15,865 --> 00:15:18,665
<i>the criminal suspect</i>
<i>represented by Xu Meng</i>

145
00:15:18,745 --> 00:15:22,945
<i>did not choose the law after being harmed.</i>

146
00:15:23,025 --> 00:15:25,825
<i>Instead, she vented her anger</i>
<i>through personal revenge.</i>

147
00:15:25,905 --> 00:15:28,585
<i>One wrong step led to another,</i>
<i>and things escalated.</i>

148
00:15:29,785 --> 00:15:33,865
<i>They kept crossing legal red lines</i>
<i>and challenging human decency,</i>

149
00:15:33,945 --> 00:15:36,305
<i>becoming perpetrators through and through.</i>

150
00:15:36,385 --> 00:15:39,305
<i>On the path of crime,</i>
<i>they went further and further,</i>

151
00:15:39,825 --> 00:15:42,385
<i>eventually sliding</i>
<i>into the abyss of no return.</i>

152
00:15:42,985 --> 00:15:45,585
<i>They have to face</i>
<i>the judgment of law and justice.</i>

153
00:15:46,985 --> 00:15:49,385
FEBRUARY 1, 2003

154
00:16:41,345 --> 00:16:43,065
I didn't know Officer Ran,

155
00:16:44,065 --> 00:16:45,745
but you said he was a good man.

156
00:16:46,785 --> 00:16:50,505
How could such a good person just be gone?

157
00:16:57,465 --> 00:16:59,345
Did you just get off the train?

158
00:17:00,745 --> 00:17:01,665
Yeah.

159
00:17:02,185 --> 00:17:03,065
Why?

160
00:17:09,464 --> 00:17:10,785
I'm going to wash my hands.

161
00:17:35,225 --> 00:17:37,745
KUNHAI→WEIYANG, FEBRUARY 1, 2003

162
00:17:56,945 --> 00:17:57,905
Sister,

163
00:17:59,145 --> 00:18:00,545
do you still want to surrender?

164
00:18:07,185 --> 00:18:10,345
If you still want to go, I'll go with you.

165
00:18:13,345 --> 00:18:16,625
I know it might be
the wrong time to say this,

166
00:18:16,705 --> 00:18:18,265
but I still want to say it.

167
00:18:19,145 --> 00:18:22,225
Officer Ran's death might have been fate.

168
00:18:22,305 --> 00:18:25,105
It's God giving you
a chance to choose again.

169
00:18:33,585 --> 00:18:34,905
From now on,

170
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:37,865
no matter what I face,

171
00:18:43,745 --> 00:18:46,185
I will choose to be a good person.

172
00:18:51,385 --> 00:18:54,145
Sister, come home with me.

173
00:18:54,665 --> 00:18:56,225
It's only safe if you leave here.

174
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:01,665
The home I wanted

175
00:19:05,425 --> 00:19:06,625
is already gone.

176
00:19:07,425 --> 00:19:09,225
The home you want doesn't matter.

177
00:19:10,745 --> 00:19:12,025
Safety is what matters.

178
00:19:16,345 --> 00:19:17,385
Meng,

179
00:19:19,665 --> 00:19:20,705
you should go.

180
00:19:26,385 --> 00:19:29,145
Aren't you afraid that staying
in Weiyang is dangerous?

181
00:19:34,225 --> 00:19:36,265
I just want to stay in the sunlight.

182
00:19:43,185 --> 00:19:45,065
Even if it's dangerous sunlight.

183
00:21:16,265 --> 00:21:18,065
SIX MONTHS LATER, WEIYANG PEOPLE'S
PROCURATORATE FILED A PUBLIC PROSECUTION

184
00:21:18,145 --> 00:21:19,985
DEFENDANT XU MENG IS SUSPECTED
OF ARSON, INTENTIONAL HOMICIDE

185
00:21:20,065 --> 00:21:22,385
AND FALSE ACCUSATION
SENTENCING RECOMMENDATION: DEATH PENALTY

186
00:21:22,465 --> 00:21:24,785
DEFENDANT QIAO SUQING IS SUSPECTED
OF INTENTIONAL HOMICIDE, HARBORING

187
00:21:24,865 --> 00:21:26,705
AND FALSE ACCUSATION; SENTENCING
RECOMMENDATION: LIFE IMPRISONMENT

188
00:21:39,865 --> 00:21:42,465
KIDDO

189
00:21:44,865 --> 00:21:47,105
It's about time.

190
00:21:47,745 --> 00:21:49,305
Why is there no news?

191
00:21:52,785 --> 00:21:53,785
WECHAT: 1 CONTACT SENT A MESSAGE

192
00:22:00,025 --> 00:22:02,665
<i>The sentencing just finished.</i>
<i>Xu got the death penalty.</i>

193
00:22:02,745 --> 00:22:04,145
<i>Qiao got life.</i>

194
00:22:29,425 --> 00:22:30,345
Hey, Meng.

195
00:22:30,865 --> 00:22:32,145
Hurry up and get up.

196
00:22:32,225 --> 00:22:33,585
Let's go for a walk downstairs.

197
00:22:33,665 --> 00:22:34,705
No.

198
00:22:34,785 --> 00:22:36,825
I'm going to practice "turtle breathing".

199
00:22:36,905 --> 00:22:38,105
"Turtle breathing," my foot.

200
00:22:38,185 --> 00:22:40,625
If you don't move around,
you'll be breathing your last soon!

201
00:22:40,705 --> 00:22:42,225
I'm not going. I'm about to fall asleep.

202
00:22:42,305 --> 00:22:44,145
Take a walk downstairs.

203
00:22:44,225 --> 00:22:45,345
No, I'm not going.

204
00:22:45,425 --> 00:22:47,185
-Let's go.
-No.

205
00:22:47,265 --> 00:22:48,385
-I said I'm not going.
-Come on.

206
00:22:48,465 --> 00:22:50,465
Help! Is anyone there?

207
00:22:50,545 --> 00:22:52,345
Manager!

208
00:22:52,425 --> 00:22:54,065
Come and change my room.

209
00:22:54,145 --> 00:22:56,825
I can't stay in the same room
as this nutcase anymore!

210
00:22:56,905 --> 00:22:59,345
-Shut up.
-Manager, where are you?

211
00:22:59,425 --> 00:23:01,025
Help. Somebody!

212
00:23:01,105 --> 00:23:01,945
Shut up.

213
00:23:02,025 --> 00:23:04,065
Didn't you say you wanted
to see the square dance?

214
00:23:04,145 --> 00:23:05,505
I'm taking you there,
and you're still unhappy?

215
00:23:08,105 --> 00:23:10,745
COMMENDATION CEREMONY
FOR THE YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH CASE

216
00:23:14,545 --> 00:23:15,505
MERIT CITATION CLASS II

217
00:23:21,065 --> 00:23:21,945
ZHAO JIE, ZOU WUHUANG

218
00:23:22,705 --> 00:23:23,665
Ms. He Xiaohe,

219
00:23:23,745 --> 00:23:26,945
on behalf of the veterans at the branch,
on my own behalf,

220
00:23:27,545 --> 00:23:29,505
and on behalf of Captain Ran,
who died in the line of duty,

221
00:23:29,585 --> 00:23:30,665
thank you.

222
00:23:41,785 --> 00:23:42,825
Congratulations.

223
00:23:45,185 --> 00:23:46,225
Thank you, Director Zou.

224
00:23:52,185 --> 00:23:53,825
SECOND-CLASS MERIT MEDAL

225
00:23:56,705 --> 00:23:57,665
Xiaohe,

226
00:23:58,905 --> 00:24:01,105
you truly are the direct disciple
of my senior.

227
00:24:01,705 --> 00:24:02,745
Starting off with a Second-Class Merit.

228
00:24:04,105 --> 00:24:06,465
But you must never get arrogant.

229
00:24:06,545 --> 00:24:07,585
You need to achieve more in the future.

230
00:24:07,665 --> 00:24:10,305
Don't worry, Captain.
I will keep working hard.

231
00:24:11,585 --> 00:24:12,425
There's also this.

232
00:24:13,025 --> 00:24:14,145
What? There's another one?

233
00:24:14,225 --> 00:24:15,665
This is for Mr. He.

234
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:17,065
An honorary certificate
for assisting in the investigation.

235
00:24:17,145 --> 00:24:18,985
You will deliver it on our behalf.

236
00:24:22,145 --> 00:24:24,625
Such an important honor,
how can it just be handed over?

237
00:24:25,345 --> 00:24:27,545
The leadership isn't even
presenting it in person?

238
00:24:28,265 --> 00:24:30,705
Is the leadership
getting too full of themselves?

239
00:24:35,745 --> 00:24:38,265
Captain, I didn't say those words
just now.

240
00:24:38,345 --> 00:24:41,385
I'm just a messenger for my dad.
Speaking for him in advance.

241
00:24:43,345 --> 00:24:45,305
Yes. He's right.

242
00:24:45,385 --> 00:24:46,745
How about this?

243
00:24:46,825 --> 00:24:49,025
When the meeting is over,
I'll take the whole team

244
00:24:49,105 --> 00:24:50,985
to pay Mr. He a visit in person
and give it to him.

245
00:24:51,065 --> 00:24:52,345
Thank you, sir!

246
00:24:58,265 --> 00:24:59,225
Wait.

247
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:05,945
This… Who is this supposed to be for?

248
00:25:06,825 --> 00:25:09,745
Ms. He Xiaohe, effective immediately,

249
00:25:09,825 --> 00:25:11,825
you are officially transferred
to criminal field operations.

250
00:25:12,345 --> 00:25:13,465
In view of your outstanding performance,

251
00:25:13,545 --> 00:25:14,785
the bureau has granted

252
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:16,825
you an opportunity
to change your badge number.

253
00:25:19,065 --> 00:25:20,225
No need, Director Zou.

254
00:25:20,305 --> 00:25:21,665
I'm fine using my own number.

255
00:25:22,265 --> 00:25:25,025
Don't you want to see
the numbers you can choose from?

256
00:25:34,905 --> 00:25:36,905
HE YUANHANG 813032

257
00:25:38,865 --> 00:25:42,345
RAN FANGXU 813081

258
00:26:40,465 --> 00:26:41,305
RAN FANGXU

259
00:26:41,385 --> 00:26:42,465
Uncle Ran,

260
00:26:43,425 --> 00:26:45,145
I have some good news for you.

261
00:26:45,745 --> 00:26:46,985
The June 30th case is solved.

262
00:26:47,705 --> 00:26:50,065
My dad and I followed the path
you took back then,

263
00:26:50,585 --> 00:26:51,825
and we solved it completely.

264
00:26:52,945 --> 00:26:54,025
From now on,

265
00:26:54,105 --> 00:26:55,985
you don't have to worry
about this case anymore.

266
00:26:56,945 --> 00:26:58,105
Oh, right.

267
00:26:59,145 --> 00:27:01,985
Director Zou said
I could change to a new badge number.

268
00:27:03,145 --> 00:27:04,785
He gave me two choices.

269
00:27:05,785 --> 00:27:06,825
One was yours,

270
00:27:07,585 --> 00:27:08,665
and the other was my dad's.

271
00:27:09,625 --> 00:27:10,505
Uncle Ran,

272
00:27:11,025 --> 00:27:12,225
I'm sorry.

273
00:27:13,345 --> 00:27:14,185
I didn't choose yours.

274
00:27:15,785 --> 00:27:17,345
But I didn't choose my dad's either.

275
00:27:17,945 --> 00:27:19,425
I still want to use my own.

276
00:27:20,825 --> 00:27:23,905
You'll support me, right?

277
00:27:35,465 --> 00:27:37,905
Back then, everyone said
my song was old-fashioned.

278
00:27:38,705 --> 00:27:39,785
Only you thought it sounded good.

279
00:27:40,545 --> 00:27:41,665
You really have good taste.

280
00:27:42,625 --> 00:27:44,505
This year, listen to it
one more time, okay?

281
00:27:44,585 --> 00:27:46,585
If you still think it's good,

282
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:47,745
then listen to it a few more times.

283
00:27:48,465 --> 00:27:51,385
If you think it's terrible,
please don't shake your head.

284
00:27:51,905 --> 00:27:53,105
I'm afraid of getting scared.

285
00:28:11,505 --> 00:28:15,025
<i>Freedom, freedom. It's burning</i>

286
00:28:15,105 --> 00:28:18,065
<i>Close your eyes. Get some rest</i>

287
00:28:18,145 --> 00:28:20,505
<i>The demolition under the spotlight</i>
<i>of the Yuanlongli community</i>

288
00:28:20,585 --> 00:28:21,825
<i>is proceeding smoothly.</i>

289
00:28:21,905 --> 00:28:25,785
<i>The building demolition work</i>
<i>will officially begin in 30 minutes.</i>

290
00:28:25,865 --> 00:28:28,585
<i>Once a high-end community in Weiyang City,</i>

291
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:30,065
<i>it will now exit the stage of history</i>

292
00:28:30,145 --> 00:28:32,225
<i>as the times continue to move forward.</i>

293
00:28:32,305 --> 00:28:34,665
<i>Many urban legends have taken place here.</i>

294
00:28:34,745 --> 00:28:38,305
<i>One wonders if they will fade into</i>
<i>the dust as this building disappears.</i>

295
00:28:38,385 --> 00:28:39,705
<i>Let us wait and see.</i>

296
00:28:39,785 --> 00:28:42,185
All checkpoints,
report your safety status.

297
00:28:43,225 --> 00:28:45,065
Checkpoint One, clear.

298
00:28:46,025 --> 00:28:47,625
Checkpoint Two, clear.

299
00:28:48,785 --> 00:28:50,465
Checkpoint Three, clear.

300
00:28:51,465 --> 00:28:52,825
Checkpoint Four, clear.

301
00:28:52,905 --> 00:28:53,745
DEMOLITION IN PROGRESS. NO ENTRY

302
00:28:53,825 --> 00:28:55,385
Checkpoint Five, clear.

303
00:28:56,305 --> 00:28:57,585
Checkpoint Six, clear.

304
00:28:58,505 --> 00:28:59,905
Checkpoint Seven, clear.

305
00:29:00,945 --> 00:29:02,345
Checkpoint Eight, clear.

306
00:29:02,425 --> 00:29:03,385
WEIYANG BLASTING SERVICES
POWERING YUANLONGLI'S DEMOLITION

307
00:29:03,985 --> 00:29:07,265
All checkpoints are clear.
Requesting detonation.

308
00:29:07,345 --> 00:29:09,305
Commencing one-minute countdown.

309
00:29:10,345 --> 00:29:11,465
Officer He,

310
00:29:12,505 --> 00:29:13,545
by coming here,

311
00:29:13,625 --> 00:29:17,025
I can still see
my own house turning into rubble.

312
00:29:17,785 --> 00:29:19,065
But what are you here for?

313
00:29:19,585 --> 00:29:22,025
Don't tell me
you just came to hear the bang.

314
00:29:32,185 --> 00:29:33,705
My judgment tells me
that the Yuanlongli case

315
00:29:33,785 --> 00:29:35,385
isn't just a prank.

316
00:29:35,905 --> 00:29:38,065
Because it's a prank. Understood?

317
00:29:38,145 --> 00:29:39,465
It wasn't a prank at all.

318
00:29:39,545 --> 00:29:42,625
They also said
the Xu Meng case was a prank.

319
00:29:42,705 --> 00:29:43,865
What did you do?

320
00:29:43,945 --> 00:29:44,905
What are you doing?

321
00:29:44,985 --> 00:29:46,705
I'll look for evidence at Yuanlongli now.

322
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:48,945
Why do you keep going to Yuanlongli?

323
00:29:49,025 --> 00:29:50,945
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

324
00:29:56,905 --> 00:29:59,545
This case has almost become a joke.

325
00:29:59,625 --> 00:30:01,065
I can't go back empty-handed.

326
00:30:01,985 --> 00:30:03,265
Stop!

327
00:30:05,985 --> 00:30:08,665
Ran Fangxu, block him! Block him quickly!

328
00:30:16,385 --> 00:30:20,025
He, I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

329
00:30:20,105 --> 00:30:23,705
I will do my best
to avoid delaying your return.

330
00:30:24,745 --> 00:30:26,865
He, are you giving up?

331
00:30:26,945 --> 00:30:29,745
Are you telling me to give up?

332
00:30:29,825 --> 00:30:31,425
How can you call this giving up?

333
00:30:31,505 --> 00:30:33,225
I'm telling you to accept
your current pace

334
00:30:33,305 --> 00:30:34,865
and you may continue to be useful.

335
00:30:34,945 --> 00:30:36,385
That's just giving up.

336
00:30:36,465 --> 00:30:38,185
That's just giving up.

337
00:30:38,265 --> 00:30:39,985
<i>I want to give it one last shot</i>

338
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:42,225
and investigate Yuanlongli again.

339
00:30:56,225 --> 00:30:59,145
<i>Why else do you think</i>
<i>I always visit Yuanlongli?</i>

340
00:30:59,225 --> 00:31:02,065
<i>Because I know</i>
<i>it has the most important lead.</i>

341
00:31:02,145 --> 00:31:04,945
As long as Yuanlongli is still here,
the case can be solved.

342
00:31:23,385 --> 00:31:25,945
-Ten.
-Ten!

343
00:31:26,025 --> 00:31:27,985
-Nine.
-Nine!

344
00:31:28,745 --> 00:31:30,265
-Eight.
-Eight!

345
00:31:31,305 --> 00:31:32,625
-Seven.
-Seven.

346
00:31:33,665 --> 00:31:34,825
-Six.
-Six.

347
00:31:35,905 --> 00:31:37,145
-Five.
-Five.

348
00:31:38,065 --> 00:31:39,025
-Four.
-Four.

349
00:31:40,065 --> 00:31:41,185
-Three.
-Three.

350
00:31:41,825 --> 00:31:42,745
-Two.
-Two.

351
00:31:44,105 --> 00:31:45,905
-One.
-Detonate.

352
00:32:17,825 --> 00:32:20,065
DEMOLITION IN PROGRESS. NO ENTRY

353
00:32:39,945 --> 00:32:42,025
Everything's been reduced to rubble.

354
00:32:43,185 --> 00:32:46,065
Officer He, did you see that?

355
00:32:59,945 --> 00:33:03,545
SENIOR WELLNESS AND CARE CENTER

356
00:33:10,785 --> 00:33:14,185
Officers, who are you here to arrest?

357
00:33:14,265 --> 00:33:16,385
Don't be nervous.
We're here to visit Mr. He Yuanhang.

358
00:33:16,905 --> 00:33:19,265
SENIOR WELLNESS AND CARE CENTER

359
00:33:24,985 --> 00:33:27,385
Mr. He, the comrades are here to see you.

360
00:33:36,345 --> 00:33:38,385
Mr. He? Are you in the bathroom?

361
00:33:48,825 --> 00:33:50,865
Sir, have you seen…

362
00:33:51,385 --> 00:33:53,705
Sir, have you seen the person
who lives in this room,

363
00:33:53,785 --> 00:33:55,025
someone named He Yuanhang?

364
00:33:55,105 --> 00:33:57,665
Mr. He, comrades from the force
are here to see you.

365
00:34:01,745 --> 00:34:04,305
Mr. He, are you okay?

366
00:34:12,945 --> 00:34:15,304
Sir, we are looking for He Yuanhang.

367
00:34:15,385 --> 00:34:17,025
Do you know where he went?

368
00:34:17,105 --> 00:34:18,784
What do you want with He?

369
00:34:18,865 --> 00:34:20,304
Meng, come out.

370
00:34:20,385 --> 00:34:22,545
We're here to deliver
an award to He Yuanhang.

371
00:34:22,625 --> 00:34:23,905
Where is he? Where did he go?

372
00:34:25,705 --> 00:34:26,945
Delivering an award?

373
00:34:27,905 --> 00:34:29,705
Well, in that case, you'll have to wait.

374
00:34:30,225 --> 00:34:32,065
He went to the railway station
to see someone off.

375
00:34:38,824 --> 00:34:40,585
The railway station? To see who off?

376
00:34:40,665 --> 00:34:42,425
Oh no. Something's wrong.

377
00:34:58,025 --> 00:34:58,985
Ran,

378
00:34:59,705 --> 00:35:01,225
when you go back to Beijing this time,

379
00:35:01,305 --> 00:35:04,065
just quit that teaching job.

380
00:35:04,665 --> 00:35:07,105
Come back to the force.
We can be partners again.

381
00:35:08,865 --> 00:35:10,945
Sir, that's a nice thought,

382
00:35:11,545 --> 00:35:12,945
but it's procedurally impossible.

383
00:35:13,025 --> 00:35:14,185
I can't return to the criminal department.

384
00:35:14,265 --> 00:35:15,665
Why not?

385
00:35:15,745 --> 00:35:17,665
Xu Zhihong's skull has been found.

386
00:35:17,745 --> 00:35:20,065
We were both in charge
of this case back then.

387
00:35:20,145 --> 00:35:22,185
If you come back,
we can keep investigating

388
00:35:22,265 --> 00:35:23,785
and drag the killer out.

389
00:35:23,865 --> 00:35:26,265
Sir, you're misremembering.

390
00:35:27,105 --> 00:35:29,345
The June 30th case is already solved.

391
00:35:29,425 --> 00:35:30,745
It's completely closed.

392
00:35:32,385 --> 00:35:33,305
That's impossible.

393
00:35:33,825 --> 00:35:36,185
If it were solved,
why would you be teaching in Beijing?

394
00:35:36,265 --> 00:35:37,865
Stop trying to fool me.

395
00:35:38,745 --> 00:35:39,745
Don't you remember?

396
00:35:40,465 --> 00:35:42,985
In the end, this case was solved
by you and Xiaohe.

397
00:35:43,585 --> 00:35:45,505
Everyone involved was brought to justice.

398
00:35:46,025 --> 00:35:47,665
They all received
the sentence they deserved.

399
00:35:49,185 --> 00:35:50,985
Actually, I should thank you both

400
00:35:51,705 --> 00:35:53,105
for helping me fulfill a long-held wish.

401
00:35:56,945 --> 00:35:58,065
No…

402
00:35:58,585 --> 00:35:59,665
You must be lying to me.

403
00:35:59,745 --> 00:36:02,865
Without you, just Xiaohe and me,

404
00:36:02,945 --> 00:36:04,465
one old and one young,

405
00:36:04,545 --> 00:36:06,105
how could we have solved
such a complex case?

406
00:36:08,705 --> 00:36:11,665
Sir, everyone is here.

407
00:36:11,745 --> 00:36:12,745
If you don't believe me, ask them.

408
00:36:18,225 --> 00:36:19,225
Mr. He.

409
00:36:20,265 --> 00:36:23,305
Are you all here to see Ran off?

410
00:36:25,545 --> 00:36:26,425
Yes.

411
00:36:27,185 --> 00:36:29,305
Fangxu, safe travels.

412
00:36:29,385 --> 00:36:31,505
Once you're in Beijing,
don't forget about us.

413
00:36:31,585 --> 00:36:33,225
Where are you looking?

414
00:36:33,305 --> 00:36:35,305
He's right here.

415
00:36:38,385 --> 00:36:39,305
Don't forget about us.

416
00:36:41,745 --> 00:36:42,665
How could I?

417
00:36:43,865 --> 00:36:46,425
Every one of you is in my heart.

418
00:36:48,305 --> 00:36:49,145
Dad!

419
00:36:53,105 --> 00:36:55,505
Xiaohe, Uncle Ran is leaving.

420
00:36:55,585 --> 00:36:57,345
Hurry up and say goodbye.

421
00:37:00,545 --> 00:37:02,745
Goodbye, Uncle Ran.

422
00:37:03,545 --> 00:37:05,425
See? We're all doing quite well.

423
00:37:05,505 --> 00:37:06,945
You can head back to Beijing in peace.

424
00:37:09,065 --> 00:37:11,185
Don't worry. I'm at ease now.

425
00:37:12,465 --> 00:37:15,465
Xiaohe, that uniform really suits you.

426
00:37:16,065 --> 00:37:18,465
Keep it up. You'll be better than me.

427
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:27,745
<i>The Beijing-bound Train Z118</i>
<i>is about to depart.</i>

428
00:37:27,825 --> 00:37:29,385
<i>Passengers, please board the train now.</i>

429
00:37:31,585 --> 00:37:33,585
Sir, I should go.

430
00:37:38,025 --> 00:37:39,985
Ran, go on then.

431
00:37:40,065 --> 00:37:41,225
But we have a deal.

432
00:37:41,745 --> 00:37:43,505
You cannot leave and never return.

433
00:37:44,265 --> 00:37:46,345
From time to time,
you must come home and visit.

434
00:37:46,425 --> 00:37:48,865
Otherwise, we will be worried about you.

435
00:37:48,945 --> 00:37:49,945
Understand?

436
00:37:51,665 --> 00:37:52,505
Okay.

437
00:37:59,585 --> 00:38:00,625
Say something.

438
00:38:00,705 --> 00:38:02,105
-Say…
-Right.

439
00:38:02,705 --> 00:38:04,185
We miss you all the time.

440
00:38:04,265 --> 00:38:05,585
We're always thinking about you.

441
00:38:06,785 --> 00:38:07,705
Captain Ran,

442
00:38:08,225 --> 00:38:09,185
I'm Zheng Zhong.

443
00:38:09,265 --> 00:38:10,505
Even though you've never met me,

444
00:38:10,585 --> 00:38:12,505
I can recite
all of your books from memory.

445
00:38:13,105 --> 00:38:15,785
The theories in those books,
to this very day,

446
00:38:15,865 --> 00:38:16,905
we are still using them.

447
00:38:21,705 --> 00:38:22,545
You hear it?

448
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:23,825
I hear you.

449
00:38:25,065 --> 00:38:26,105
I hear all of you.

450
00:38:28,185 --> 00:38:29,785
Thank you for still
keeping me in your thoughts.

451
00:38:30,425 --> 00:38:32,745
And I wish you success in your work

452
00:38:34,505 --> 00:38:35,385
and good health.

453
00:38:37,905 --> 00:38:38,865
I'm going now.

454
00:38:48,905 --> 00:38:49,865
Sir,

455
00:38:51,585 --> 00:38:52,425
I'm leaving.

456
00:40:13,065 --> 00:40:15,665
Ran Fangxu has truly left this time!

457
00:40:16,185 --> 00:40:18,345
Take care of yourselves.

458
00:40:38,705 --> 00:40:40,625
I really do miss Captain Ran.

459
00:40:45,345 --> 00:40:46,505
I always have.

460
00:40:48,585 --> 00:40:51,305
Don't worry, Uncle Ran.

461
00:40:53,025 --> 00:40:54,105
I will carry it on.

462
00:40:56,225 --> 00:40:57,425
We'll carry it all on.

463
00:40:59,025 --> 00:41:01,025
Goodbye!

464
00:42:24,425 --> 00:42:30,545
THE END

